description:
This place has been a hot spot for me and my friends for as long as I've been in the city.  It's perfect after a night out enjoying the "spirits" at any of the local bars nearby, or if you are just looking for some comfort food, Los Panchos is sure to brighten Your spirits. ( ; 

The papusas are the best in town, period.  The salsa and salad is just right with the warm tortilla-like breading and filling of your choice (my favorite is beans and cheese).  Makes me hungry just thinking about it.   

The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is because the service is kind of slow, but the wait is definitely worth it.  And, hey, patience is a virtue, right?
